sql:
SELECT author_name FROM authors WHERE is_organization = 1
UNION
SELECT user_name FROM users WHERE role = 'admin';

SELECT plugins.plugin_name, authors.author_name
FROM plugins
INNER JOIN authors ON plugins.author = authors.author_id;

SELECT COUNT(update_id) AS number_of_updates
FROM plugin_updates
WHERE update_date >= '2020-01-01' AND update_date <= '2020-12-31';

external_knowledge:
- 'architects' refers to the 'author' of plugins;
- 'planted seeds' metaphorically means 'contributed core plugins';
- 'garden of core components' metaphorically describes the set of core plugins in the system;
- 'from the most prolific to the least' indicates ordering by the number of contributions in descending order.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT u.user_name
FROM users u
JOIN plugins p ON u.user_name = p.installation_date;

SELECT plugin_name, last_checked_for_update 
FROM plugins 
WHERE last_checked_for_update > DATE('now', '-30 days');
